manned interplanetary spaceflight, and we like the martians possess dircted energy weapons ( laser weapons , and neutral particle beam weapons ) some of which are similar<br>
to the martian heat ray used by the martians  in the War Of the Worlds. We are also capable of creating military siege machines on land  that could be similar to those of the martians.  We can create rocket propelled space  planes<br>
like those of the martians .  We have also been using jet propelled fighter planes that are something like  those of the martians since the 1950s. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/uprojectorion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>projectorion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Nuclear Renaissance Man</span><br>  Posts: 540<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(2/27/02 6:56:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=15.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.fas.org/nuke/hew/Usa/Tests/Rwmohawk2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Science fictional civilizations and reality</span><hr size=1> Fiction is often based on what we know. Practically everything in H.G.Wells novel 'War of the Worlds' was extrapolated science and H.G. was far more imaginative than most writers, including Verne in my opinion. His 'time machine' remains to me one of the most original science fiction creations of all time. <br>
I'm not diminishing his work as I believe it had a profound impact on scientific thinking but lasers have been around a very long time. We have long dreamed of interplanetary spaceflight but are little closer than Wells's time to achieving it I think.<br>
Jet planes are a lot swifter than the ponderous machines described as used by the Martian invaders. However, the Martians obviously utilised a power source capable of keeping their craft going for days and weeks while a jet fighter can only stay aloft a few short hours before refuelling. If we are almost on a par with the technology in 'war of the Worlds' then we will achieve it when we apply nuclear power to aircraft. A reactor could generate enough power for both long flights AND death rays.  <p>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
<br>Nuclear power is the next logical step for serious space travel. The technology required to colonise the solar system exists now!

